9. Success / failure flag for next SSIS package
Back on Control Flow, outside the Sequence Container:

Add Execute SQL Task: SQL_SetStatus_Success.

Connection: CM_CES_SQL.

SQLStatement:

sql
EXEC [SBCES].[usp_SetInterfaceStatus]
     'CES_IFS',
     'SUCCESS',
     NULL;
Precedence constraint: from SEQ_Load_CES_From_IFS to this task, green (Success) only.

Add Execute SQL Task: SQL_SetStatus_Fail.

Connection: CM_CES_SQL.

SQLStatement:

sql
EXEC [SBCES].[usp_SetInterfaceStatus]
     'CES_IFS',
     'FAIL',
     'FAILED – see SBCES.Errors for details';
Precedence constraint: from SEQ_Load_CES_From_IFS to this task, red (Failure) only.

Now:

Next SSIS package can check:

sql
SELECT LastStatus, LastRunDateTime, LastErrorDesc
FROM [SBCES].[InterfaceStatus]
WHERE InterfaceName = 'CES_IFS';
and only run if LastStatus = 'SUCCESS'.
